abstract: A federal judge is expected to approve the $26 billion deal imminently. The bankers will be happy; California and New York officials, not so much.
snippet: A federal judge is expected to approve the $26 billion deal imminently. The bankers will be happy; California and New York officials, not so much.
lead_paragraph: Voting in New Hampshire’s Democratic primary has begun, and Mike Bloomberg has won over one small town. Meanwhile, Pete Buttigieg is gaining support from business moguls. (Want this in your inbox each morning? Sign up here.)

headline_main: What’s at Stake in the New Hampshire Primary
byline_original: By Reid J. Epstein and Adriana Ramić

abstract: Joe Biden had spent much of the weekend ahead of New Hampshire's primary on Tuesday attacking his top Democratic presidential rivals when a young woman asked why voters should believe he could win a national election after his poor showing in Iowa.
snippet: Joe Biden had spent much of the weekend ahead of New Hampshire's primary on Tuesday attacking his top Democratic presidential rivals when a young woman asked why voters should believe he could win a national election after his poor showing in Iowa...
lead_paragraph: HAMPTON, N.H. — Joe Biden had spent much of the weekend ahead of New Hampshire's primary on Tuesday attacking his top Democratic presidential rivals when a young woman asked why voters should believe he could win a national election after his poor showing in Iowa.
headline_main: Biden Shows Tenderness and Temper on 2020 Presidential Trail
headline_print_headline: Biden Shows Tenderness and Temper on 2020 Presidential Trail

abstract: The candidate keeps talking about winning “unwinnable fights.” But the New Hampshire primary was not supposed to be in that category.
snippet: The candidate keeps talking about winning “unwinnable fights.” But the New Hampshire primary was not supposed to be in that category.
lead_paragraph: CONCORD, N.H. — Two days before a once-mission-critical primary in a state she neighbors, Senator Elizabeth Warren — typically exceptional at holding a room — had not finished speaking when something unusual happened: Dozens of voters began filtering out of the middle school gym she had reserved.
